============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is democracy?
A1: Democracy is government where power derives from the
     people through free elections, rule of law, and
     protection of minority rights. Types include direct and
     representative democracy.

Q2: What is machine learning?
A2: Machine learning enables systems to learn from
     experience without being explicitly programmed, using
     data to improve performance automatically.

Q3: What is metabolism?
A3: Metabolism is all chemical reactions in an organism
     that maintain life: catabolism (breaking molecules for
     energy) and anabolism (building complex molecules from
     simple ones).

Q4: What is the Magna Carta?
A4: The Magna Carta (1215) was a charter limiting royal
     power in England, establishing that the king is subject
     to law. It influenced modern constitutional law and
     human rights.

Q5: What is the internet?
A5: The internet is a global network of interconnected
     computers using TCP/IP protocols. It began as ARPANET
     in 1969 and became public with the World Wide Web in
     1994.

